        "text": "Rarely. Even an offer that feels insulting is a signal that a buyer exists and is interested enough to put a number on paper. The more productive response is to counter at a price that reflects your position clearly, without slamming the door. Rejecting outright removes your ability to negotiate and rarely improves your outcome."
      }
