    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much below asking price is a lowball offer?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "In Brisbane's inner east, offers more than 8 to 10 percent below asking price are generally considered low. But whether an offer is genuinely low or simply realistic depends on how your property is priced relative to comparable recent sales. An offer that looks low on an overpriced listing may actually reflect fair market value."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What should I do if I receive a low offer shortly after listing?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Counter with confidence if your pricing is supported by comparable sales, and ask your agent to identify what is driving the low offer. Early low offers can sometimes reflect genuine buyer interest from someone hoping to secure the property before competition develops. Do not make a significant concession on price at this stage without understanding the full buyer picture."
